76    * current process. The minimal configuration which is required to draw a process via the
77    * {@link ProcessDrawer} can be achieved by calling the following setters:
78    * <ul>
79    * <li>{@link #setDisplayedChain(OperatorChain)}</li>
80    * <li>{@link #setProcesses(ExecutionUnit[])}</li>
81    * <li>{@link #setProcessSize(ExecutionUnit, Dimension)} (see
82    * {@link ProcessDrawUtils#calculatePreferredSize(ProcessRendererModel, ExecutionUnit, int, int)} to
83    * automatically create the correct dimensions for each {@link ExecutionUnit} of a process)</li>
84    * </ul>
85    * <p>
86    * Note that the model itself does not fire any events. To trigger events, call any of the fireXYZ
87    * methods. This is done for performance reasons and to support batch updates and only trigger
88    * events when really needed.
89    * </p>
90    *
91    * @author Marco Boeck, Jan Czogalla
92    * @since 6.4.0
93    *
94    */

374    public Exception undo() {...
375    if (!hasUndoSteps()) {
376    return null;
377    }
378    if (!hasRedoSteps()) {
379    // add redo step from current state

381    undoManager.add(true);

385    }

396    /**

398    * problem occurred, {@code null} otherwise.
399    *

401    * @see #setToStep(int)
402    * @since 7.5
403    */
 
- Uncovered Elements: 0 (0) Complexity: 1 Complexity Density: -
404    public Exception redo() {...
405    if (!hasRedoSteps()) {
406    return null;
407    }
408    undoIndex++;
409    Exception result = setToStep(undoIndex);
410    if (!hasRedoSteps()) {
411    // remove last step since we are at the end of stack
412    // undo will create a redo step that represents the state at the time of undo
413    undoManager.removeLast();
414    }
415    return result;
416    }
